"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Carotid endarterectomy in asymptomatic men",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 299px; height: 462px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    In the ACAS trial, 1662 patients with an asymptomatic carotid stenosis &ge;60 percent were randomized to medical therapy with aspirin or carotid endarterectomy (CEA) and followed for a mean of 2.2 years.",
"    <br>",
"     (Top panel) There was no difference between the two groups in the incidence of major stroke or death.",
"     <br>",
"      (Bottom panel) The incidence of any ipsilateral TIA or stroke or death was lower in the surgical group (p = 0.004).",
"      <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"      </div>",
"      <div class=\"reference\">",
"       Data from: Executive Committee for the Asymptomatic Carotid Atherosclerosis Trial. JAMA 1995; 273:1421.",
